ZH: 今天早晨草地上覆盖着一层霜。
EN: There was a layer of frost covering the grass this morning.

ZH: 霜冻把花朵都冻坏了。
EN: The frost froze all the flowers.

ZH: 外面的植物被霜覆盖得银白一片。
EN: The plants outside were covered in a blanket of silver frost.

ZH: 霜对果树的影响非常大。
EN: Frost has a big impact on fruit trees.

ZH: 他的车窗上被霜冻住了。
EN: Frost froze his car windows shut.

ZH: 这片土地上的霜还没有化。
EN: The frost on this land hasn't melted yet.

ZH: 这是我第一次在花园里看到那么多霜。
EN: This is the first time I've seen so much frost in the garden.

ZH: 今晚的天气预报说会有霜。
EN: The weather forecast for tonight says there will be frost.

ZH: 霜使得墙壁上的涂料脱落。
EN: Frost caused the paint on the walls to peel off.

ZH: 霜对庄稼生长有负面影响。
EN: Frost has a negative impact on crop growth.

ZH: 我们需要提前做好防霜准备。
EN: We need to make preparations in advance to prevent frost.

ZH: 来自北方的风带来了一场霜。
EN: A frost was brought by the wind from the north.

ZH: 早晨出去要注意地面上的霜，以免滑倒。
EN: Be careful of the frost on the ground when going out in the morning to prevent slipping.

ZH: 霜过后，树叶会变得透明。
EN: After the frost, the leaves will become transparent.

ZH: 霜的到来意味着夏季的结束。
EN: The arrival of frost signifies the end of summer.

ZH: 我们用遮盖物保护花园里的植物免受霜冻侵害。
EN: We use covers to protect the plants in the garden from frost damage.

ZH: 从霜中走出来的感觉真是令人宽慰。
EN: The feeling of walking out of the frost is truly comforting.

ZH: 霜在地面上形成了美丽的图案。
EN: Frost formed beautiful patterns on the ground.

ZH: 这片园地的地面被一层薄霜覆盖着。
EN: The ground of this garden is covered with a thin layer of frost.

ZH: 昨晚窗外的树叶上结了霜。
EN: Frost formed on the leaves outside the window last night.
